					<div class="post-info">
						<p>
							<span class="time">October 18, 2012</span>
															<span class="author">by <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/author/mktgeistmike/" title="Posts by mktgeistmike" rel="author">mktgeistmike</a></span>
																						<span class="post-comments"><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2012/10/18/australian-gold-sales-to-china-soar-900-silverdoctors/#comments" title="Comment on AUSTRALIAN GOLD SALES TO CHINA SOAR 900%&nbsp;[silverdoctors]">1 Comment</a></span>
																				</p>
					</div>

					<p>While Congress argues over labeling China a currency manipulator, China is busy continuing to massively increase their physical gold and silver reserves.Â <strong>The Australian reports that Aussie gold exports to China have soared a mind-blowingÂ 900% over the first 8 months of 2012 to $4.1 billionÂ asÂ <em>Chinese buyers are hoarding the precious metal</em>.</strong></p>
<p><strong><em>Sales soar 900pc as China makes grab for Aussie gold</em></strong><br />
<em>GOLD has soared past coal as Australiaâs second most valuable physical export to China, withÂ <strong>sales up a whopping 900 per cent for the first eight months of the year, bringing in $4.1 billion.</strong></em></p>
