			<div class="post-6757 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-gold category-silver">

				<div class="entry">

					<h2><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2012/09/09/coordinated-central-bank-action-is-behind-golds-recent-advance-notes-jim-sinclair-arabianmoney/">Coordinated central bank action is behind goldâs recent advance notes Jim Sinclair&nbsp;[arabianmoney]</a></h2>

					<div class="post-info">
						<p>
							<span class="time">September 9, 2012</span>
															<span class="author">by <a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/author/mktgeistmike/" title="Posts by mktgeistmike" rel="author">mktgeistmike</a></span>
																						<span class="post-comments"><a href="http://blog.mktgeist.com/2012/09/09/coordinated-central-bank-action-is-behind-golds-recent-advance-notes-jim-sinclair-arabianmoney/#respond" title="Comment on Coordinated central bank action is behind goldâs recent advance notes Jim Sinclair&nbsp;[arabianmoney]">Leave a comment</a></span>
																				</p>
					</div>

					<div><img title="jim-sinclair11" src="http://www.arabianmoney.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/jim-sinclair11.jpg" alt="" width="243" height="175" /></div>
<p>Gold superbug Jim Sinclair, whose price forecasts have been the most consistently accurate for more than a decade, has noted that coordinated action by global central banks is the main explanation for the recent price hike in precious metals with gold now on the road to $3,500 an ounce.</p>
<p>âIf you have eyes to see, coordinated central bank monetary and fiscal stimulation action is taking place,â his weekly missive to his many folloers said. âYesterday was âDraghi Day.â Today the Chinese officially released massive fiscal stimulus on top of the already monetary stimulus. Watch for the US Fed to chime in.</p>
<p><strong>QE to infinity</strong></p>
<p>âQE to infinity MOPEd as sterilized is falling into place. Please review my post from last weekend to you on the illusion of monetary sterilization. Gold is going to and through $3500.</p>
<p>âThe approach some long term gold bulls took toward gold, initiating a temporary short directly after Labor Day, is now in the process of backfiring badly.â Thatâs a reminder that staying long and staying strong is often a much better approach than trying to trade the gold bull market.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.arabianmoney.net/gold-silver/2012/09/08/coordinated-central-bank-action-is-behind-golds-recent-advance-notes-jim-sinclair/">Read more</a></p>
<div class="clear"></div>

				</div>

